
IRSA (Identity and Access Management (IAM) Roles for Service Accounts)
- Allows pods to have IAM roles associated with them via a kubernetes service account

- Allows you to use IAM to assign fine-grained permissions to pods to allow them to access AWS resources

- Removes the need to embed AWS credentials into your applications or store them as secrets on the cluster

- Utilizes OIDC

EKS Pod Identity
- New way of interracting with AWS resources

- Simplifies trust policy principals and removes the need to configure an OIDC provider for your cluster

- Requires the use of a newer version of the AWS SDK which many applications don't support yet

